  "prompt": "What are some things that doctors know, but most people don't?",
  "response": "Here are some medical insights that many doctors understand, but the general public might not:\n\n1. Most common illnesses are viral and don't require antibiotics\n\n2. Diagnostic tests aren't always definitive and can have false positives/negatives\n\n3. Lifestyle changes are often more effective than medication for many chronic conditions\n\n4. The human body has remarkable self-healing capabilities\n\n5. Many symptoms can have multiple potential causes\n\n6. Mental health significantly impacts physical health\n\n7. Early prevention is far more effective than treating advanced disease\n\n8. Nutrition plays a massive role in overall health and disease prevention\n\n9. Genetics and family history are crucial in understanding personal health risks\n\n10. The placebo effect is real and powerful\n\n11. Most medical research is probabilistic, not absolute\n\n12. Sleep, stress management, and social connections are critical to health\n\n13. Minor symptoms can sometimes indicate serious underlying conditions\n\n14. Medical professionals often don't know everything and continue learning\n\n15. Patient communication and trust are as important as medical knowledge\n\n16. Side effects are common with many medications\n\n17. The human immune system is incredibly complex and not fully understood\n\nThese insights reflect the nuanced understanding medical professionals develop through education, experience, and ongoing research.",
